  "texts": [
    "For simple models, the choices made in lemmatizing and stop word removal can have a large influence on model outcomes [12].Dependency parsing is another processing step enhanced by tagged parts of speech.",
    "These methods analyse grammatical structure to tag relationships between different words in a sentence.",
    "This allows for many downstream tasks such as identifying the subjects of sentences, who is doing what action, or where and when events are occuring.",
    "Similarly, part of speech tags can help when words are spelled the same but have different meanings depending on context (e.g.",
    "words used as either a verb or a noun: \"bark\", \"breed\", \"control\", \"flower\"), or sets of words that represent a concept or a formal group."
  ],
